The Biden-Harris Administration has made racial equity a priority since day one, directing every federal agency to address systemic racism's lasting impacts on Black communities. They have implemented policies to create economic opportunities for Black Americans, such as expanding access to small business ownership and increasing federal contracting from disadvantaged businesses. The administration has also focused on ensuring equitable educational opportunities, improving health outcomes, reforming the criminal justice system, and protecting voting rights. They have taken steps to reduce barriers faced by Black communities in the aftermath of natural disasters. The administration plans to continue promoting equity and racial justice for Black Americans as they work to build a better future.